{
  "texts": [
    "4 and 5 estimate a function that quantifies the impact of specific training examples on a given model or prediction.",
    "For the most part, these methods take an ablation perspective, i.e., measuring how much a model changes",
    "when removing specific training examples.",
    "However, there are several other research areas related to analyzing the impact of different subsets of the training data, albeit with somewhat different methods or objectives.",
    "We briefly describe some of these topics below."
  ]
}